      • showInputDialog

        public boolean showInputDialog​(java.awt.Frame parent,
                               java.lang.String title,
                               java.lang.String message,
                               java.lang.String[] names,
                               java.lang.Class<?>[] types)
        Displays an input dialog box, centered with respect to the given parent window frame (unless the parent is null), with the given window title text and message displayed, along with a set of labeled text boxes for reading input of the given types.
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent window about which to center (centered with respect to the entire screen if parent is null)
        title - text to show in window's title bar
        message - message to display in the window above its inputs
        names - names of each input to display
        types - type of each input (strings, boolean checkboxes, etc.)
        Returns:
        true if the User clicks OK, false if the user cancels.

      • showInputDialog

        public boolean showInputDialog​(java.awt.Frame parent,
                               java.lang.String title,
                               java.lang.String message,
                               java.lang.String[] names,
                               java.lang.Class<?>[] types,
                               java.lang.Object[] initialValues)
        Displays an input dialog box, centered with respect to the given parent window frame (unless the parent is null), with the given window title text and message displayed, along with a set of labeled text boxes for reading input of the given types.
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent window about which to center (centered with respect to the entire screen if parent is null)
        title - text to show in window's title bar
        message - message to display in the window above its inputs
        names - names of each input to display
        types - type of each input (strings, boolean checkboxes, etc.)
        initialValues - the initial value to put into each input field
        Returns:
        true if the User clicks OK, false if the user cancels.
